The paper deals with algorithms for finding maximum flows in planar graphs with multiple sources and sinks, which is a problem in graph theory and optimization. The use of planar graphs suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The mention of integer capacities and the use of algorithms that work for bounded capacities suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Finally, the mention of running times and the use of polylogarithmic factors suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
